HEADWORD: Sandix
<hw>San"dix</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sandix</ets>, <ets>sandyx</ets>, vermilion, or a color like
vermilion, Gr. <?/, <?/.]</ety> <def>A kind of minium, or red lead, made
by calcining carbonate of lead, but inferior to true minium.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>sandyx</asp>.]</altsp> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

